title: Welcome
content:
Keet provides APIs for any website. You can use us to connect your customers' accounts and perform actions on their behalf.
Call API endpoints to request data from your users accounts on websites that dont normally offer them in code as simple as:

title: Its quick and easy to get started
content:
Users connect their accounts using our link component




Access your end users accounts and act on their behalf
We offer a variety of API abstractions to make it easy to interact with your users accounts. However, we also understand there are some integrations that require more niche interactions. In that case we give you the option to connect via playwright and write your own automations.

h2.title: Its quick and easy to get started

title: Why does this exist?
content:
Building automations on sites with authenticated sessions is challenging.
Imagine if you could easily...
Get your users health data from their insurance provider.

Book Ubers based on your users calendar and location

Track activity on properties for future homeowners on Redfin

title: How are we different
content:
There are other solutions out there. What do we do differently...
No chrome extension necessary for your users to authenticate

We maintain your users authenticated sessions

Many of our API abstractions don’t rely on playwright or browser automations.

title: Add Keet Link to Your Product
content:
If you get stuck at any point, email for help at zack@trykeet.com. If you don't get a response in 10 minutes, we'll
buy you coffee.
Keet link uses a series of token exchanges to authenticate your users accounts.


    Step 1: Get a linkToken so that you can initialize a link session for your users
    Step 2: Make Keet Link appear in your frontend using the linkToken
    Step 3: Swap the publicToken, returned by keetLink for an accountToken
    Step 4: Use the accountToken for future requests to authenticated sessions.

h2.title: Add Keet Link to Your Product

title: Step 1: Get a Link Token (Server side)
content:
In your backend, set up a POST request to initialize a Keet Link session and get a linkToken from this URL: https://api.trykeet.com/v1/link/token

title: Step 2: Make the Keet Link Appear (Client side)
content:
Install the link sdk: npm install @keet-tech/react-keet-link

Use the linkToken from Step 1 to open Keet link






Install the link sdk: 

 npm install --save @keet-tech/react-native-keet-link react-native-svg

Use the linkToken from Step 1 to open Keet link:

code_snippets.code:
<button id="open-link-button">Start linking</button>
<script src="https://cdn.trykeet.com/initialize.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript">
  const button = document.getElementById("open-link-button");
  button.disabled = true;

function onSuccess(public_token) {
// Send public_token to server (Step 3)
}

KeetLink.initialize({
  // Replace ADD_GENERATED_LINK_TOKEN with the token retrieved from your backend (Step 1)
  linkToken: "ADD_GENERATED_LINK_TOKEN",
  onSuccess: (public_token) => onSuccess(public_token),
  onReady: () => (button.disabled = false),
  });

  button.addEventListener("click", function () {
  KeetLink.openLink();
});
</script>

title: Step 3: Swap publicToken for accountToken (Server Side)
content:
In your backend, create a request to exchange the short-lived publicToken for a permanent accountToken.






Store this account token someplace secure. It is used to make all requests to this end users authenticated sessions.

title: You're done!
content: Use the accountToken to make all future requests on behalf of the user to every integration they use.

h2.title: Add Keet Link to Your Product

title: Overview
content:
Integrations with Keet are designed to be super simple for you to link a single end-user to many integrations. Every end-user can have multiple Keet integrations and still has the same accountToken. 


You should store your accountToken in your database and use it to link your end-users to their Keet integrations.

title: Making requests to integrations
content:
Any time you need to make a request to an integration associated with a user you will need to pass the accountToken in the header of your request by setting X-Account-Token. 


Example

title: You can use playwright or puppeteer to take actions on your users behalf
content:
If you want to write your own automations using playwright to act on your users behalf you can do that by connecting to the playwright instance over CDP.


Venmo is used here as an example but every integration offers the endpoint POST: /session to get a websocket url to
connect via playwright or puppeteer.

h3.title: You can use playwright or puppeteer to take actions on your users behalf

title: Get a websocket url to connect to playwright
content: You can then use this wsUrl to connect to the playwright instance over CDP.

title: Using Our Abstractions
content: Using our API abstractions is extremely simple. Just include the accountToken you received from the following the Link flow in the X-Account-Token header of your requests.
